<H1>Conditional statements</H1>

<P>Every Unix command returns a value on exit which the
shell can interrogate.  This value is held in the
read-only shell variable <SAMP>$?</SAMP>.</P>

<P>A value of <SAMP>0</SAMP> (zero) signifies success; anything other than
<SAMP>0</SAMP> (zero) signifies failure.</P>

